<br>
&quot;Why did they pick ME to go to Thurgadin? Its SO cold over there. My poor feet will never be warm again. *sigh*&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;day in and day out, Nellen do this Nellen do that. I'm a good lookin halfling ya know? I should be modeling not running errands. But somehow I am stuck with delivering this...this... THING to Thurgadin. Oh well. Where IS that boat? First its too hot here in NRO then its WAY to cold in the Iceclad Ocean.&quot;<br>
<br>
Some time later...<br>
<br>
&quot;ooh.... owwww...... its to cold&quot; Nellen says with chattering teeth.&quot;I need a fire. Where is a fire? MUST find a fire!&quot;<br>
<br>
Suddenly the ground begins to shake violently. But its a measured pace; much like a.......<br>
<br>
&quot;GIANT!!!!!!!!! RUN ME RUN!&quot;<br>
<br>
As our intrepid young halfling takes off at a run he feels the giant lumber into a shambling trot that is too fast by half. Nellen knows that he cant outrun this one. What to do...<br>
Quicker than thought Nellen turns around and runs back at the giant! No... not AT the giant, but between his legs. He turns around and beings to cast......<br>
<br>
&quot;Karana hear me. Bring forth roots from the ground to slow this foe so that I may live to serve you!&quot;<br>
<br>
As the last word is spoken the ground once again begins to tremble. But this time brown creepers come out of the ground. First just a few small ones but they get bigger and bigger until they are the size of centuars.<br>
<br>
&quot;got him! those roots will hold and snare him while I make good on my escape!&quot;<br>
<br>
So our young hero takes off as fast as possible, determined to put some space between him and the lumbering giant. As he starts to run away he hears a tremendous ripping sound and looks back over his shoulder......just in time to see a chunk of root come flying by just over his head. If he would've been just a little taller.....<br>
<br>
&quot;WHAT THE ???!!!!! Those were supposed to hold! Problem. BIIIIIIG problem. What to do.....&quot;<br>
<br>
As the enraged giant starts to move again Nellen stops in prayer once more....<br>
<br>
&quot;Karana hear me. bring forth the power of the skies and blast this being back to the day he was made!&quot;<br>
<br>
Storm clouds gather out of a clear sky. Lightning lances to the earth with ear shattering intensity. The bolts dont even bother the giant. But Nellen knows that the last one will......<br>
As the storm gathers itself for the final blow Nellen notices a small glimmer around the giant......<br>
<br>
The lightning seems to creep down from the sky. foot by foot. inch by inch. everything slows down. Nellen watches in horror as the bolt heads directly for the giants chest. It hits.......and is reflected off! but its now coming straight for Nellen! He throws himself aside as the bolt sizzles past and blasts a 100 year old tree to splinters. Time is running out for Nellen.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have one last chance. I dont want to go anywhere near Kael but...... no time to plan. it'll have to work&quot;<br>
<br>
So Nellen starts to run for Kael. but he doesnt head down the ramp when he gets there. he heads along the cliff that lines the walls into the keep. And then he stops and waits. The giant grins in anticipation of his next meal who now has nowhere to run.<br>
<br>
&quot;Me eat joo!&quot; the giant roars as he lunges for Nellen.<br>
<br>
But our brave young adventurer has one last trick up his sleeve.<br>
<br>
As the giant reaches out and overbalances himself Nellen lets his last spell go. A raging tornado rises out of nowhere, and slams into the back of the giant, knocking it off balance. It stands on the edge of the precipice windmilling its arms, trying not to fall to its death.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who's the tough guy now eh? I'll teach you to pick on halflings!&quot; and with that Nellen gives the giant a small push on the back of his foot and watches with a grim satisfaction as the giant disappears into the depths.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank Karana thats over! Now to get to Thurgadin!&quot;<br>
<br>
The rest of the trip passes uneventfully and our adventurer reaches the safety of Thurgadin and Icewell keep. Safe, warm, and tired. <br>
<br>
And so the story comes to a close. Did this happen? or is it all a lie? you decide.<br>
<br>
